                    <p>
                        Candidate being added who are already a Lead/Account will trigger a duplicate warning.
                        <br><br>
                        <span style="color:red;"><strong>If there is a duplicate warning - please review duplicate candidate(s). The system is checking for the same first name, last name and email.</strong></span><br>
                        If they match - use the existing Leads profile to conduct interview and be sure to change the Lead Owner to your name. DO NOT CREATE A NEW LEAD also beware it could be a FORMER STUDENT/PROSPECTIVE STUDENT profile made by the admin team. In that case you will need to follow the process of a Former Student/Prospective Student by creating a unique new lead.
                        <br><br>
                        If candidate does not match - you can exit popup screen.
                        <br><br>


                    <h5>Scenarios for Continuing with Next Steps if there is a Closed Missed duplicated Lead/Accounts</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Depends on why the candidate is Closed Missed. If they missed because of tech skills about 3 months ago and reschedules/passes - okay with moving forward.<br></li>
                        <br>
                        <li>If they miss by personality, personality can be interpreted differently by different HR interviewers - okay with moving forward.<br></li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
