                        <br><br>
                    <h5>Former Student/Prospective Student Profile</h5>
                        We found a bug in SF - but fret not, there is a workaround (for now - hopefully not forever).
                        <br><br>
                        Directions:<br>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If you are not already, please make sure you are asking if the candidate is a former student (there’s a field in SF for this).</li>
                        <li>If they ARE a former student please put +ta or +instructor at the end of their email</li>
                        i.e. if  you were interviewing Jon, you’d put: jcaviness+ta@trilogyed.com
                        <li>If candidate will not convert to HR Passed it could be because they were a prospective student and already in the system. You want to change their email to jcaviness+@trilogyed.com before passing them to HR Passed.</li>
                    </ol>
                        <br><br>
                        <h5>Why?:</h5>
                        If we have a former student/perspective student, there is already  a student account associated with the candidate. Even if we create an Instructional account for them, SF will favor the first account which will mess with our information. For now, the work around is +ta and +instructor or + after the email.
                        <br><br>
                        The dev team is working on a solution, but for now - we are hacking the system.
                        <br><br>
                        Example of what a Former Student/Prospective Student profile would look like:
